In [12]:
def getAmazonSearch(search_query):
    url="https://www.amazon.in/s?k="+search_query
    print(url)
    page=requests.get(url,cookies=cookie,headers=header)
    if page.status_code==200:
        return page        ### creating function for the query(pass in to the getAmazonSearch function) 
    else:
        return "Error"
    #print(page.content)

<script>
    var originalOnError = window.onerror || function () {};
    var JS_SCRIPT_ERROR = 'Script error.';
    var SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER = 's-script-error';

    window.onerror = function onerror (message, file, line, col, error) {
        // Since "Script error." is what browsers send to the onerror callback when an error originates from a JavaScript
        // file served from a different origin, it doesn't have any actionable data. Hence log a counter instead of letting
        // it go to JSFatal bucket which will pollute it.
        if(message === JS_SCRIPT_ERROR && ue && ue.count) {
            ue.count(SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER, (ue.count(SCRIPT_ERROR_COUNTER) || 0) + 1);
            return;
        }

        originalOnError(message, file, line, col, error);
    };
</script>

</h5>
<div class="a-row a-spacing-small"><span class="a-color-secondary">Oct 30, 2019 - 5 Recommendations</span></div><div class="a-row a-spacing-medium"><span class="a-size-base a-color-base"><span class="a-truncate" data-a-max-rows="15" data-a-overflow-marker="&amp;hellip;" data-a-word-break="normal" style="line-height: 1.3em !important; max-height: 19.5em;"><span class="a-truncate-full">Headphones have evolved with steady maturity over the past few years, and the audio industry in India now offers a wide range of brands that cater to the budget segment in this category. These range from popular brands such as Sennheiser and JBL, to relatively newer entrants such as Boat and Boult Audio. Within Rs 1,500, you can now pick from wired and wireless headphones, and also choose between on-ear and in-ear monitors. def foot(search_query):
    url="https://www.amazon.in/dp/"+search_query
    print(url)
    page=requests.get(url,cookies=cookie,headers=header)
    if page.status_code==200:###  get url if amazon page has content it prints
        return page
    else:
        return "Error"
    #print(page.content)

def review(search_query):                     
    url="https://www.amazon.in"+search_query       ## review function pass serch_query
    #print(url)                                      ### get url
    page=requests.get(url,cookies=cookie,headers=header)   ### request to the amazon server
    if page.status_code==200:
        return page
    else:
        return "Error"

        response=review(link[j]+'&pageNumber='+str(k))     ### pass link and page number  through review
#beautifulsoup is a package
        soup=BeautifulSoup(response.content)
        for i in soup.findAll("span",{'data-hook':"review-body"}):   ## class tag of the review body
            revi.append(i.text)
